ttp://dbpedia.org/resource/Eric_Liddell\"}, {\"begin\": 351, \"end\": 358, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9967577434538921, \"rank\": 0.0014188766017815576, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But on the 100thanniversary of his great success, it is the sprinter's links to China which are being remembered.\", \"from\": 371, \"to\": 484, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 451, \"end\": 456, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999999781180124, \"rank\": 8.81438326248945e-09, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The country where he was born and died celebrates Liddell not only as a sportsman but also as a humanitarian, a teacher and even a war hero.\", \"from\": 486, \"to\": 626, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 536, \"end\": 543, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chuck_Liddell\", \"score\": 0.9999527069181952, \"rank\": 4.6431039523126616e-05, \"text\": \"Liddell\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chuck_Liddell\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chuck_Liddell\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"PARIS OLYMPIC STAR  Liddell was born on 16th January,1902 in Tianjin, North China, the son of missionaries from the London Mission Society.\", \"from\": 628, \"to\": 767, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 642, \"end\": 646, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Disney_Star\", \"score\": 0.9980375664332406, \"rank\": 0.0019662922841748275, \"text\": \"STAR\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Disney_Star\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Disney_Star\"}, {\"begin\": 648, \"end\": 655, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chuck_Liddell\", \"score\": 0.9999527069181952, \"rank\": 4.6431039523126616e-05, \"text\": \"Liddell\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chuck_Liddell\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chuck_Liddell\"}, {\"begin\": 689, \"end\": 696, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tianjin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.113591950803339e-21, \"text\": \"Tianjin\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tianjin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tianjin\"}, {\"begin\": 744, \"end\": 758, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London_Missionary_Society\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"London Mission\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London_Missionary_Society\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London_Missionary_Society\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Around the age of six he was sent to the UK to boarding school and subsequently attended Edinburgh University where he gained a reputation as the fastest man in Scotland.\", \"from\": 769, \"to\": 939, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 810, \"end\": 812, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9999999529277386, \"rank\": 4.628176626302705e-08, \"text\": \"UK\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 858, \"end\": 878, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Edinburgh\", \"score\": 0.9999999999627107, \"rank\": 3.751343756993535e-11, \"text\": \"Edinburgh University\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Edinburgh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Edinburgh\"}, {\"begin\": 930, \"end\": 938, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scotland_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.5463118723766393, \"rank\": 0.8303840080629984, \"text\": \"Scotland\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scotland_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scotland_national_rugby_union_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"His speed also led him to represent Scotland at rugby.\", \"from\": 941, \"to\": 995, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 977, \"end\": 985, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scotland_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.5463118723766393, \"rank\": 0.8303840080629984, \"text\": \"Scotland\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scotland_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scotland_national_rugby_union_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He played seven times and scored tries in four successive matches.\", \"from\": 996, \"to\": 1062, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Eric Liddell with his brother Rob at Eltham College in June 1908.\", \"from\": 1064, \"to\": 1129, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1064, \"end\": 1076, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eric_Liddell\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0206371029304016e-75, \"text\": \"Eric Liddell\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eric_Liddell\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eric_Liddell\"}, {\"begin\": 1101, \"end\": 1115, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eltham_College\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.0551735883207565e-37, \"text\": \"Eltham College\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3914\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eltham_College\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eltham_College\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"/The Eric Liddell Community  Selected to participate the in the 1924 Olympics, Liddell would have been among the favorites for the showcase 100 meter dash.\", \"from\": 1130, \"to\": 1285, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1209, \"end\": 1216, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chuck_Liddell\", \"score\": 0.9999527069181952, \"rank\": 4.6431039523126616e-05, \"text\": \"Liddell\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chuck_Liddell\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chuck_Liddell\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But, as a devout Christian, he dropped out of the event because the qualifying heats were scheduled for a Sunday.\", \"from\": 1286, \"to\": 1399, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1303, \"end\": 1312, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9930674637112872, \"rank\": 0.00698092750403588, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Instead, he switched to the 200 and 400-meter sprints.\", \"from\": 1400, \"to\": 1454, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"At the Games, despite being drawn in the challenging outside line against a powerful field, he triumphed in the 400-meters in an Olympic and World Record time of 47.6 seconds.\", \"from\": 1456, \"to\": 1631, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He also claimed a bronze medal in the 200 meters.\", \"from\": 1632, \"to\": 1681, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"LIDDELL AND CHINA  After the Olympics, Liddell turned down the opportunity of a sporting career in the UK and returned to China to pursue his parents' vocation as a missionary.\", \"from\": 1683, \"to\": 1859, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1722, \"end\": 1729, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chuck_Liddell\", \"score\": 0.9999527069181952, \"rank\": 4.6431039523126616e-05, \"text\": \"Liddell\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chuck_Liddell\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chuck_Liddell\"}, {\"begin\": 1786, \"end\": 1788, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9999999529277386, \"rank\": 4.628176626302705e-08, \"text\": \"UK\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 1805, \"end\": 1810, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999999781180124, \"rank\": 8.81438326248945e-09, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"His first job was as a teacher at an Anglo-Chinese College where he used his athletic experience to train boys in a number of different sports.\", \"from\": 1860, \"to\": 2003, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1897, \"end\": 1918, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ying_Wa_College\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Anglo-Chinese College\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ying_Wa_College\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ying_Wa_College\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He set up football, basketball, softball, baseball, ping pong, tennis and volleyball teams in Tianjin.\", \"from\": 2004, \"to\": 2106, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2098, \"end\": 2105, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tianjin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.113591950803339e-21, \"text\": \"Tianjin\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tianjin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tianjin\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"During his time in the city, Liddell also helped build the Minyuan Stadium in Tianjin which was modelled on London's Stamford Bridge, his favourite sports ground.\", \"from\": 2108, \"to\": 2270, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2137, \"end\": 2144, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chuck_Liddell\", \"score\": 0.9999527069181952, \"rank\": 4.6431039523126616e-05, \"text\": \"Liddell\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chuck_Liddell\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chuck_Liddell\"}, {\"begin\": 2186, \"end\": 2193, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tianjin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.113591950803339e-21, \"text\": \"Tianjin\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tianjin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tianjin\"}, {\"begin\": 2216, \"end\": 2222, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9998862637754804, \"rank\": 0.00011374906563360474, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The stadium became one of the leading multi-disciplinary sports venues in Asia.\", \"from\": 2271, \"to\": 2350, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"When in 1936, China formed its first Olympic delegation to participate in the Berlin Olympics, Liddell was appointed as the chief coach.\", \"from\": 2352, \"to\": 2488, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2366, \"end\": 2371, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999999781180124, \"rank\": 8.81438326248945e-09, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 2447, \"end\": 2454, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chuck_Liddell\", \"score\": 0.9999527069181952, \"rank\": 4.6431039523126616e-05, \"text\": \"Liddell\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chuck_Liddell\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chuck_Liddell\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Liddell graduated with a BSc in Science from Edinburgh University in 1924.\", \"from\": 2490, \"to\": 2564, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2490, \"end\": 2497, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chuck_Liddell\", \"score\": 0.9999527069181952, \"rank\": 4.6431039523126616e-05, \"text\": \"Liddell\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chuck_Liddell\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chuck_Liddell\"}, {\"begin\": 2535, \"end\": 2555, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Edinburgh\", \"score\": 0.9999999999627107, \"rank\": 3.751343756993535e-11, \"text\": \"Edinburgh University\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Edinburgh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Edinburgh\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"/The Eric Liddell Community  By 1941, life in China had become so dangerous because of the threat from the invading Japanese that the British government advised its nationals to leave.\", \"from\": 2565, \"to\": 2749, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2611, \"end\": 2616, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999999781180124, \"rank\": 8.81438326248945e-09, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 2681, \"end\": 2689, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japanese_people\", \"score\": 0.759957471577476, \"rank\": 0.1861745996292062, \"text\": \"Japanese\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japanese_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japanese_people\"}, {\"begin\": 2699, \"end\": 2717, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.8898993859023532, \"rank\": 0.11311880429701858, \"text\": \"British government\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Liddell, however, refused and instead joined up with his brother, serving as a doctor at a village in Hebei, North China.\", \"from\": 2751, \"to\": 2872, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2751, \"end\": 2758, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chuck_Liddell\", \"score\": 0.9999527069181952, \"rank\": 4.6431039523126616e-05, \"text\": \"Liddell\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chuck_Liddell\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chuck_Liddell\"}, {\"begin\": 2853, \"end\": 2858, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hebei\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.14624833467115e-16, \"text\": \"Hebei\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hebei\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hebei\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There he offered medical treatment to locals suffering from the hardships of a country under attack.\", \"from\": 2873, \"to\": 2973, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And even after his capture and internment at the Weixian prisoner camp (now in East China's Weifang city), Liddell took on a leadership role helping the elderly and infirm and teaching science to children.\", \"from\": 2975, \"to\": 3180, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3024, \"end\": 3031, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Weifang\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Weixian\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Weifang\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Weifang\"}, {\"begin\": 3067, \"end\": 3074, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Weifang\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Weifang\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Weifang\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Weifang\"}, {\"begin\": 3075, \"end\": 3079, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/City\", \"score\": 0.9987222712670707, \"rank\": 0.0012793629866528612, \"text\": \"city\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/City\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/City\"}, {\"begin\": 3082, \"end\": 3089, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chuck_Liddell\", \"score\": 0.9999527069181952, \"rank\": 4.6431039523126616e-05, \"text\": \"Liddell\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chuck_Liddell\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chuck_Liddell\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He died on 21 February 1945, five months before liberation, suffering from a brain tumor, overwork, and malnourishment.\", \"from\": 3182, \"to\": 3301, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"CONNECTING BRITAIN AND CHINA  Liddell was buried in the garden behind the Japanese officers' quarters and the site was forgotten until it was rediscovered in 1989.\", \"from\": 3303, \"to\": 3466, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3333, \"end\": 3340, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chuck_Liddell\", \"score\": 0.9999527069181952, \"rank\": 4.6431039523126616e-05, \"text\": \"Liddell\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chuck_Liddell\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chuck_Liddell\"}, {\"begin\": 3377, \"end\": 3385, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japanese_people\", \"score\": 0.759957471577476, \"rank\": 0.1861745996292062, \"text\": \"Japanese\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japanese_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japanese_people\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The prisoner-of-war camp is now a place of learning for 2,000 Chinese teenagers.\", \"from\": 3468, \"to\": 3548, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3530, \"end\": 3537, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9997260800900011, \"rank\": 0.00025373171961106343, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Liddell at Stamford Bridge shortly after his Olympic win.\", \"from\": 3550, \"to\": 3607, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3550, \"end\": 3557, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chuck_Liddell\", \"score\": 0.9999527069181952, \"rank\": 4.6431039523126616e-05,